Love the fact that Barney's sunk his teeth into Fizzy Mustafiz, but he's more than just a cutter/slower ball merchant. The guy really knows how to use the left-armer's natural angle to right-handers and his control, for a 20-year-old, is exquisite. He's not express, but he can get it up to 140-142kph or thereabouts, and he showed against South Africa that he can hack it in Tests as well. I don't know if this is actual memory or me projecting what I want to see onto hazy remembrances, but I think he swung the new ball into the right-handers as well, on his Test debut.



