You can't bowl a doosra with a straight arm. The laws now allow a certain amount of flex so that you can just about bowl a legal doosra. Other countries tolerate bowlers around the legal limit in the hope that one or too will eventually be able to bowl legally in international cricket. But in the UK we play it safe and discourage anyone who bowls with a noticeably bent arm, whether they are legal or not.



